ex.html:695:          if (versions.includes(coordinates.version)) {\n./stats/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-scripting-compiler-embeddable/2.3.21/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./metadata/io.ktor/ktor-client-logging-jvm/index.json:14:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./stats/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-server/12.0.1/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/com.google.api.grpc/grpc-google-cloud-spanner-executor-v1/6.116.1/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/org.slf4j/jul-to-slf4j/1.7.30/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-ee/12.0.10/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./metadata/io.ktor/ktor-client-content-negotiation-jvm/index.json:14:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./stats/com.google.api.grpc/proto-google-iam-v1/1.40.1/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/com.github.ghostdogpr/caliban_3/2.10.0/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/com.google.api.grpc/proto-google-cloud-bigquerystorage-v1alpha/3.14.1/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/org.jboss.arquillian.container/arquillian-container-test-api/1.1.10.Final/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/com.google.api.grpc/proto-google-cloud-spanner-admin-instance-v1/6.116.1/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:44:- An artifact-level `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json` that records, per metadata version: tested library versions, allowed packages, source/test/documentation URLs, optional `requires`, `default-for`, `skipped-versions`, and `override` flags.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:52:- Validation of `index.json` schema and `metadata-version`/`tested-versions` integrity.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:101:| `library-bulk-update` | PR | PR records newly tested upstream versions for already-supported libraries when no repair is required. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:137:    NBT->>NBT: for each application dependency,<br/>pick metadata version via index.json<br/>(tested-versions → default-for → latest)\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:161:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries; each entry's required fields are `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\"<group>:<artifact>\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:163:The schema follows semver, and **minor- and patch-version bumps** (e.g., `v2.0.1` → `v2.0.2` or `v2.0.x` → `v2.1.0`) are guaranteed to be backward-compatible with native-build-tools. Minor bumps add new optional fields used by the website, the test harness, or future tooling (`requires`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, `repository-url`); patch bumps refine validation of those same auxiliary fields. The plugin reads only the six fields enumerated above, so an older native-build-tools release continues to resolve metadata correctly against any newer minor or patch version of the schema. Only a **major-version bump** can break the contract, which NFR-4 forbids — schema changes are additive only.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:169:1. `v ∈ tested-versions` → use that entry's `metadata-version` directory directly.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:172:If neither matches and the user has enabled `useLatestVersion` on the query (Gradle: `useLatestMetadataVersion()`), the plugin falls back to the entry with `latest: true` (at most one per file, FR-M-6). Otherwise no metadata is loaded for that coordinate. `skipped-versions` is consumed by the test harness and the libraries-and-frameworks page, not by the plugin at native-image time.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:177:    LoadIndex --> Tested{\"Any entry with<br/><code>v ∈ tested-versions</code>?\"}\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:193:Auxiliary contracts: `requires` triggers the plugin to also load metadata for the listed `group:artifact` pair; `override: true` instructs the plugin to suppress any built-in metadata that ships inside `native-image` itself for the matched versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:205:- **FR-M-5** Each `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/` directory must include a valid `index.json` enumerating its metadata versions and tested library versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:206:- **FR-M-6** Exactly one entry in a non-empty `index.json` must carry `latest: true`. If a library version is not in `tested-versions`, the harness selects an entry by matching the optional `default-for` regex.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:212:- **FR-T-2** Tests live under `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>` unless an `index.json` entry sets `test-version` to share a suite across versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:213:- **FR-T-3** Tests must not pin to specific library versions or bypass the library's public API in ways that would mask metadata gaps. Scaffold-only tests are not acceptable.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:216:- **FR-T-6** Newly added `tested-versions` entries are recorded in `index.json` only after they pass on **every** required environment (enforced by `verify-new-library-version-compatibility`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:217:- **FR-T-7** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:236:- **FR-CI-5** `verify-new-library-version-compatibility` caps each scheduled run at a fixed library budget and at most 30 newer versions per library, expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, and creates one aggregated GitHub issue per failed `(library, version)` pair.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:265:- An `index.json` describing metadata versions and tested versions.\n./stats/org.jboss.arquillian.container/arquillian-container-test-api/1.1.11.Final/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/org.slf4j/log4j-over-slf4j/1.7.25/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/org.jline/jline-terminal-jni/3.30.7/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./stats/com.google.api.grpc/proto-google-cloud-bigquerystorage-v1beta/3.14.1/stats.json:2:  \"versions\" : [ {\n./metadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm/index.json:14:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./metadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm/index.json:14:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./docs/CI.md:17:- A single source of truth for which Java versions and OS runners to test on.\n./docs/CI.md:28:  - Uses: [`generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) with base/head SHAs to test only what changed. It batches each changed metadata version's [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) into chunks of up to 30 versions per job, then pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, and runs only that batch.\n./docs/CI.md:29:- Test new library versions ([.github/workflows/test-new-library-versions.yml](../.github/workflows/test-new-library-versions.yml))\n./docs/CI.md:31:  - Uses: [`generateChangedTestedVersionsMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to compute only newly added [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) from the base/head diff and pairs them with the matching [`metadata-version`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json), then runs [`run-consecutive-tests.sh`](../.github/workflows/scripts/run-consecutive-tests.sh) only for those added versions.\n./docs/CI.md:43:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\n./docs/CI.md:59:Once eligible, the workflow extracts the requested Maven coordinates from the issue title, validates the `groupId:artifactId:version` format, closes invalid requests, closes duplicate exact-coordinate requests, and closes requests for versions already supported by the repository. If the request remains eligible, it generates a deps.dev dependency graph and opens or reuses `library-new-request` issues for unsupported transitive dependencies, linking them as blockers of the original request.\n./metadata/io.ktor/ktor-server-websockets-jvm/index.json:14:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./metadata/io.ktor/ktor-test-dispatcher-jvm/index.json:14:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./metadata/io.ktor/ktor-network-tls-certificates-jvm/index.json:14:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./metadata/io.ktor/ktor-server-test-host-jvm/index.json:14:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./metadata/io.ktor/ktor-server-sessions-jvm/index.json:14:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./metadata/avalon-framework/avalon-framework/index.json:10:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./metadata/org.mongodb/mongo-java-driver/index.json:10:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./metadata/org.mongodb/mongo-java-driver/index.json:48:    \"tested-versions\" : [\n./stats/com.typesafe.play/play_2.13/2.9.10/stats.json:2:  \"versions\